    "what_description": "Mniodes subspicata is a perennial plant belonging to the family Asteraceae, native to North America. It has basal leaves that are lanceolate, 2-4 cm long, and toothed, with the upper leaves being smaller and not toothed. The plant produces small, pink to purple flower heads, 1-2 cm in diameter, with 8-15 florets, and is dioecious, meaning it has separate male and female plants. The flower heads are arranged in a corymbiform inflorescence, and the plant grows 5-20 cm tall. Mniodes subspicata typically blooms from June to September, producing achenes as fruit.",
